Outlayer removal¶

In [14]:
# Define a function to remove outliers using the IQR method
def remove_outliers_iqr(df, column):
    Q1 = df[column].quantile(0.25)
    Q3 = df[column].quantile(0.75)
    IQR = Q3 - Q1
    lower_bound = Q1 - 1.5 * IQR
    upper_bound = Q3 + 1.5 * IQR

    df_filtered = df[(df[column] >= lower_bound) & (df[column] <= upper_bound)]
    return df_filtered

# List of columns to remove outliers from
columns_to_filter = ['ph', 'Hardness', 'Solids', 'Chloramines', 'Sulfate', 'Conductivity', 'Organic_carbon', 'Trihalomethanes', 'Turbidity']

# Remove outliers for each specified column
for column in columns_to_filter:
    df = remove_outliers_iqr(df, column)

# Save the dataset with outliers removed
df.to_csv('outliers_removed_water_potability.csv', index=False)

from sklearn.preprocessing import MinMaxScaler

# Read the dataset with outliers removed
df = pd.read_csv('outliers_removed_water_potability.csv')

# Select the columns to scale (excluding 'Potability' column)
columns_to_scale = ['ph', 'Hardness', 'Solids', 'Chloramines', 'Sulfate', 'Conductivity', 'Organic_carbon', 'Trihalomethanes', 'Turbidity']

# Initialize the Min-Max scaler
scaler = MinMaxScaler()

# Fit and transform the selected columns using Min-Max scaling
df[columns_to_scale] = scaler.fit_transform(df[columns_to_scale])

# Save the scaled dataset
df.to_csv('scaled_water_potability.csv', index=False)

from sklearn.metrics.pairwise import cosine_similarity

# Read the scaled dataset
df = pd.read_csv('scaled_water_potability.csv')

# Extract the feature columns (excluding the 'Potability' column)
features = df.drop('Potability', axis=1)

# Calculate the cosine similarity matrix
similarity_matrix = cosine_similarity(features)

# Create a DataFrame from the similarity matrix
similarity_df = pd.DataFrame(similarity_matrix, index=df.index, columns=df.index)

# Display the similarity matrix

GUI¶

In [25]:
import PySimpleGUI as sg
import pickle

# Load the pre-trained Random Forest model
with open('SVM_model.pkl', 'rb') as model_file:
    model = pickle.load(model_file)
sg.theme('BlueMono')
# Define the layout of the GUI
layout = [
    [sg.Text('Enter Water Parameters:')],
    [sg.Text('pH:'), sg.InputText(key='ph')],
    [sg.Text('Hardness:'), sg.InputText(key='hardness')],
    [sg.Text('Solids:'), sg.InputText(key='solids')],
    [sg.Text('Chloramines:'), sg.InputText(key='chloramines')],
    [sg.Text('Sulfate:'), sg.InputText(key='sulfate')],
    [sg.Text('Conductivity:'), sg.InputText(key='conductivity')],
    [sg.Text('Organic Carbon:'), sg.InputText(key='organic_carbon')],
    [sg.Text('Trihalomethanes:'), sg.InputText(key='trihalomethanes')],
    [sg.Text('Turbidity:'), sg.InputText(key='turbidity')],
    [sg.Button('Predict Potability')],
    [sg.Button('Reset')],
    [sg.Button('Terminate')],
    [sg.Text('', size=(20, 1), key='potability_result')]
]

window = sg.Window('Water Potability Prediction', layout,size=(700, 400))

while True:
    event, values = window.read()

    if event == sg.WIN_CLOSED or event == 'Terminate':
        break
    elif event == 'Predict Potability':
        try:
            # Extract the input values and convert them to float
            input_data = [float(values['ph']), float(values['hardness']), float(values['solids']),
                          float(values['chloramines']), float(values['sulfate']), float(values['conductivity']),
                          float(values['organic_carbon']), float(values['trihalomethanes']), float(values['turbidity'])]

            # Make a prediction using the model
            prediction = model.predict([input_data])

            # Display the result
            result = "Potable" if prediction[0] == 1 else "Non-Potable"
            window['potability_result'].update(f'Potability: {result}')
        except ValueError:
            window['potability_result'].update('Invalid input. Please enter valid numbers.')
    elif event == 'Reset':
        window['ph'].update('')
        window['hardness'].update('')
        window['solids'].update('')
        window['chloramines'].update('')
        window['sulfate'].update('')
        window['conductivity'].update('')
        window['organic_carbon'].update('')
        window['trihalomethanes'].update('')
        window['turbidity'].update('')
        window['potability_result'].update('')

window.close()

End of the Report¶
